    <header>
      <div class="title">Aho Jin Shashanam</div>
      <!--div class="subtitle">उत्तर का शत्रुंजय तीर्थ</div-->
      <img class="coverimg" src="/static/images/timeline/ahojinshashan.jpeg" alt="Aho Jin Shashanam"/>
      <div class="description">
        2577 years ago today, Shraman Bhagwan Mahavir established four-fold Sangha on the day of Vaishakh Shukla 11 in Pavapuri. Although there were grave dangers to Jain Dharma for two thousand years from the Nirvana of Lord Veer due to the ill effects of the planet Bhasma, but history testifies that Jain Dharam has a glorious history. Thousands of episodes in Jain scriptures are written in golden letters. Some instances are presented to inspire us. :-
      </div>
      <div class="p-2">
        <a href='/timeline/en/ahojinshashan'>Eng</a> | <a href='/timeline/hi/ahojinshashan'>हिंदी</a>
      </div>
    </header>
  
      <div class= "flex-lg-fill col">
      <div class="timeline">
        <div class="timeline__bar"></div>
        <div class="d-flex justify-content-center p-2" style="position: relative;
        ">
          <div class="note note-primary" style="max-width:300px;">
            
            <strong>This Year </strong>
            <ul>
              <li>2021 AD</li>
              <li><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vira_Nirvana_Samvat">VNS( Vir Nirvan Samvat)</a> 2547 </li>
              <li><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vikram_Samvat">Vikram Samvat</a> 2077   </li>
            </ul>
            
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="timeline__event timeline__eventtype-default">
          <div class="timeline__event-date">
              -30 VNS
          </div>
          <div class="timeline__event-title text-center">Shasan Sthapana</div>
          
          <!-- ASPECT RATIO 16:9, DIMENSION OF IMAGES SHOULD BE 320X180 -->
          <img class="timeline__event-image" src="/static/images/timeline/ShasanSthapna.jpg" alt="Shasan Sthapana"/>
          
          <!-- DESCRIPTION SHOULD BE LESS THAN 270 CHARACTERS -->
          <div class="timeline__event-descr">At the age of 42, Shraman Bhagwan Mahavir established Chaturvidh Sangh on the day of Vaishakh Shukla 11 in Pavapuri. Indrabhuti and other distinguished 11 Brahmins were assigned the rank of Gandhar. Chandanbala became the first Sadhviji, Anand etc. shravak and revati etc.. shravika.</div>
          
          <div class="timeline__event-actions">
            <a 
              class="timeline__event-action" 
              href="https://www.historyofjainism.com/timeline/shraman-parampara/shashan-sthapna" 
              title="Learn More">
                Read More
            </a>
          </div>
          
        </div>
        
        <div class="timeline__event timeline__eventtype-default">
          <div class="timeline__event-date">
              0 VNS
          </div>
          <div class="timeline__event-title text-center">First Head of Monks</div>
          
          <!-- ASPECT RATIO 16:9, DIMENSION OF IMAGES SHOULD BE 320X180 -->
          <img class="timeline__event-image" src="/static/images/timeline/SudharmaSwami.jpg" alt="First Head of Monks"/>
          
          <!-- DESCRIPTION SHOULD BE LESS THAN 270 CHARACTERS -->
          <div class="timeline__event-descr">Nine Gandhars attained salvation before Lord Mahavir Swami. Lord&#x27;s Nirvana was followed by Gautamswamiji&#x27;s Nirvana. For this reason, his disciple tradition came under the guidance of Fifth Gandhar Sudharma Swamiji. For this reason the current Shramana tradition belongs to Sudharmaswamiji</div>
          
          <div class="timeline__event-actions">
            <a 
              class="timeline__event-action" 
              href="https://www.historyofjainism.com/timeline/shraman-parampara/pratham-pattadhar" 
              title="Learn More">
                Read More
            </a>
          </div>
          
        </div>
        
        <div class="timeline__event timeline__eventtype-default">
          <div class="timeline__event-date">
              2 VNS
          </div>
          <div class="timeline__event-title text-center">Shrimal and Porwal community</div>
          
          <!-- ASPECT RATIO 16:9, DIMENSION OF IMAGES SHOULD BE 320X180 -->
          <img class="timeline__event-image" src="/static/images/timeline/Swayamprabhsuri.jpg" alt="Shrimal and Porwal community"/>
          
          <!-- DESCRIPTION SHOULD BE LESS THAN 270 CHARACTERS -->
          <div class="timeline__event-descr">The fifth Pattadhar  of Sri Parshwanath Bhagavan, Sri Swayamprabhasuri went to a yagna (a ritual done in front of a sared fire) which was held in Srimal Nagri and Padmavati Nagri and preached to the king and his subjects and turned 135,000 house-bearers Jain and henceforth established the Shrimal an</div>
          
          <div class="timeline__event-actions">
            <a 
              class="timeline__event-action" 
              href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/16ogCwik-6CNfEthQF3rdEpkfjf4KBXcS/view?usp=sharing" 
              title="Learn More">
                Read More
            </a>
          </div>
          
        </div>
        
        <div class="timeline__event timeline__eventtype-gyan">
          <div class="timeline__event-date">
              64 VNS
          </div>
          <div class="timeline__event-title text-center">Last Kevali</div>
          
          <!-- ASPECT RATIO 16:9, DIMENSION OF IMAGES SHOULD BE 320X180 -->
          <img class="timeline__event-image" src="/static/images/timeline/Jambuswami.jpg" alt="Last Kevali"/>
          
          <!-- DESCRIPTION SHOULD BE LESS THAN 270 CHARACTERS -->
          <div class="timeline__event-descr"> Jambuswami was the last kevali of this Avsarpini period in Bharat region. Hearing the sermon of Sri Sudharmaswamy at the age of 16, he accepted celibacy. After 20 years of diksha, he attained kevalgyan and spending 44 years as Kevali he attained salvation at the age of 80 years.</div>
          
          <div class="timeline__event-actions">
            <a 
              class="timeline__event-action" 
              href="https://www.historyofjainism.com/timeline/shraman-parampara/nirgranth-gana#h.hnqxgzwda8wz" 
              title="Learn More">
                Read More
            </a>
          </div>
          
        </div>
        
        <div class="timeline__event timeline__eventtype-default">
          <div class="timeline__event-date">
              70 VNS
          </div>
          <div class="timeline__event-title text-center">Oswal Community</div>
          
          <!-- ASPECT RATIO 16:9, DIMENSION OF IMAGES SHOULD BE 320X180 -->
          <img class="timeline__event-image" src="/static/images/timeline/Ratnaprabhsuri.jpg" alt="Oswal Community"/>
          
          <!-- DESCRIPTION SHOULD BE LESS THAN 270 CHARACTERS -->
          <div class="timeline__event-descr">The 6th Pattadhar of Shri Parshwanath Bhagavan, Sri Ratnaprabhasuri established the Upkesh community by teaching 1,80,000 Kshatriyas in Upkesh Nagar. Upkesh Nagar later began to be called as Osian and this community Oswal. Also, Oswal, Porwal and Srimal were popularly known as Mahajan.</div>
          
          <div class="timeline__event-actions">
            <a 
              class="timeline__event-action" 
              href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/16ogCwik-6CNfEthQF3rdEpkfjf4KBXcS/view?usp=sharing" 
              title="Learn More">
                Read More
            </a>
          </div>
          
        </div>
        
        <div class="timeline__event timeline__eventtype-gyan">
          <div class="timeline__event-date">
              160 VNS
          </div>
          <div class="timeline__event-title text-center">First council of Agam</div>
          
          <!-- ASPECT RATIO 16:9, DIMENSION OF IMAGES SHOULD BE 320X180 -->
          <img class="timeline__event-image" src="/static/images/timeline/AgamVachna1.png" alt="First council of Agam"/>
          
          <!-- DESCRIPTION SHOULD BE LESS THAN 270 CHARACTERS -->
          <div class="timeline__event-descr">After 12 years of drought, the Shramana Sangh under the guidance and leadership of Shri Sthulibhadra held the first agam council in Veer Nirvana Samvat 160 at Pataliputra. He collected 11 aagams and to learn the 12th Anga Sri Sthulibhadra and other munis went to Sri Bhadrabahu Swami.</div>
          
          <div class="timeline__event-actions">
            <a 
              class="timeline__event-action" 
              href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1Bityx6qGbEMNxBAtm3ruyXsg0QNGTSi5/view" 
              title="Learn More">
                Read More
            </a>
          </div>
          
        </div>
        
        <div class="timeline__event timeline__eventtype-gyan">
          <div class="timeline__event-date">
              222 VNS
          </div>
          <div class="timeline__event-title text-center">Last Shrutkevali</div>
          
          <!-- ASPECT RATIO 16:9, DIMENSION OF IMAGES SHOULD BE 320X180 -->
          <img class="timeline__event-image" src="/static/images/timeline/bhadrabahuswami.jpg" alt="Last Shrutkevali"/>
          
          <!-- DESCRIPTION SHOULD BE LESS THAN 270 CHARACTERS -->
          <div class="timeline__event-descr">Shri Prabhav, Sri Shayambhav, Sri Yashobhadra, Shri Sambhut, Shri Bhadrabahu and Shri Sthulabhadra, these six are known as Shrutakevali because they knew all 14 purvas. Shri Bhadrabahu was the last shrut kevali who knew both Sutra and meaning and Shri Sthulabhadra knew only Sutra of last 4 purvas.</div>
          
          <div class="timeline__event-actions">
            <a 
              class="timeline__event-action" 
              href="https://medium.com/muni-speaks/shrut-kevali-284b27e08923" 
              title="Learn More">
                Read More
            </a>
          </div>
          
        </div>
        
        <div class="timeline__event timeline__eventtype-mandir">
          <div class="timeline__event-date">
              292 VNS
          </div>
          <div class="timeline__event-title text-center">Construction of 1.25 lakh Jain temples</div>
          
          <!-- ASPECT RATIO 16:9, DIMENSION OF IMAGES SHOULD BE 320X180 -->
          <img class="timeline__event-image" src="/static/images/timeline/samprati.jpg" alt="Construction of 1.25 lakh Jain temples"/>
          
          <!-- DESCRIPTION SHOULD BE LESS THAN 270 CHARACTERS -->
          <div class="timeline__event-descr">Learning how he attained the kingdom by the grace of Arya Suhasti, his benefactor from previous birth, Samprati Maharaja built 1.25 lakh jain temples, 1.25 crore statues, 95,000 metal statues, renovated 36000 jain temples and graced the land of India with 700 charitable institutions.</div>
          
          <div class="timeline__event-actions">
            <a 
              class="timeline__event-action" 
