                Read More
            </a>
          </div>
          
        </div>
        
        <div class="timeline__event timeline__eventtype-raja">
          <div class="timeline__event-date">
              470 VNS
          </div>
          <div class="timeline__event-title text-center">Vikram Samvat</div>
          
          <!-- ASPECT RATIO 16:9, DIMENSION OF IMAGES SHOULD BE 320X180 -->
          <img class="timeline__event-image" src="/static/images/timeline/vikramaditya.jpg" alt="Vikram Samvat"/>
          
          <!-- DESCRIPTION SHOULD BE LESS THAN 270 CHARACTERS -->
          <div class="timeline__event-descr">Shri Siddheshna Diwakar Suri brought forth the idol of Shri Avanti Parshwanath by composing the Sri Kalyan Mandir Stotra. In this way by enlightening him Vikram Raja became a devout Jain. He established his own calendar which is called Vikram Samvatsar.</div>
          
          <div class="timeline__event-actions">
            <a 
              class="timeline__event-action" 
              href="https://www.historyofjainism.com/timeline/shraman-parampara/prabhavak-acharya#h.6ma47aiad6aj" 
