        <div class="timeline__event timeline__eventtype-gyan">
          <div class="timeline__event-date">
              830 VNS
          </div>
          <div class="timeline__event-title text-center">4th Agam Vachna</div>
          
          <!-- ASPECT RATIO 16:9, DIMENSION OF IMAGES SHOULD BE 320X180 -->
          <img class="timeline__event-image" src="/static/images/timeline/AgamVachna4.png" alt="4th Agam Vachna"/>
          
          <!-- DESCRIPTION SHOULD BE LESS THAN 270 CHARACTERS -->
          <div class="timeline__event-descr">At that time there was a period of turbulence - hegemony of Buddhists in Saurashtra and war between Huns and Gupts in North. Later, Shiladityas won in Vallabhi and Guptas conquered Mathura. Shramana congregated under the guidance of Nagarjunasuri in Mathura and Skandil Suri in Vallabhi.</div>
          
        </div>
        
        <div class="timeline__event timeline__eventtype-gyan">
          <div class="timeline__event-date">
              980 VNS
          </div>
          <div class="timeline__event-title text-center">5th Agam Vachnan</div>
          
          <!-- ASPECT RATIO 16:9, DIMENSION OF IMAGES SHOULD BE 320X180 -->
          <img class="timeline__event-image" src="/static/images/timeline/AgamVachna5.jpg" alt="5th Agam Vachnan"/>
          
          <!-- DESCRIPTION SHOULD BE LESS THAN 270 CHARACTERS -->
          <div class="timeline__event-descr">The 5th Agam Vachna was held under the direction of Shri Devardhigini Shamashraman and Acharya Bhootdinna. For the first time, the Aagams were written down. In the gathering, 84 verses, niyrukti, bhashya, kampyapadi and elemental sutras and crores of shlokes were written.</div>
          
        </div>
        
        <div class="timeline__event timeline__eventtype-gyan">
          <div class="timeline__event-date">
              983* VNS
          </div>
          <div class="timeline__event-title text-center">Kalpasutra Open Preaching</div>
          
          <!-- ASPECT RATIO 16:9, DIMENSION OF IMAGES SHOULD BE 320X180 -->
          <img class="timeline__event-image" src="/static/images/timeline/Kalpasutra.jpg" alt="Kalpasutra Open Preaching"/>
          
          <!-- DESCRIPTION SHOULD BE LESS THAN 270 CHARACTERS -->
          <div class="timeline__event-descr">Senapati Bhattarak became the king of Vallabhi by taking advantage of the weakness of the Gupta dynasty. His son Dhruvasen came t the throne of Vallabhi. He followed Jainism. Kalpasutra&#x27;s first open sermon were given in Kumarabhukti Nagar, Anandpur to console a mourning Dhruvsen over death of his so</div>
          
        </div>
        
        <div class="timeline__event timeline__eventtype-raja">
          <div class="timeline__event-date">
              1272 VNS
          </div>
          <div class="timeline__event-title text-center">Establishment of Patan</div>
          
          <!-- ASPECT RATIO 16:9, DIMENSION OF IMAGES SHOULD BE 320X180 -->
          <img class="timeline__event-image" src="/static/images/timeline/patan.jpg" alt="Establishment of Patan"/>
          
          <!-- DESCRIPTION SHOULD BE LESS THAN 270 CHARACTERS -->
          <div class="timeline__event-descr">Vanaraj established Anhilpur Patan and constructed the temple of Panchasara Parshwanath Bhagwan. Acharya Shilgunsuri played an important role in the rise of Vanaraj. Vanraj was fully supported by the Jains - brave Chamraj, Nina and Ashak were Jain ministers of Vanaraja</div>
          
          <div class="timeline__event-actions">
            <a 
              class="timeline__event-action" 
              href="https://medium.com/muni-speaks/the-glory-of-patan-f3c84954f895" 
              title="Learn More">
                Read More
            </a>
          </div>
          
        </div>
        
        <div class="timeline__event timeline__eventtype-mandir">
          <div class="timeline__event-date">
              1558 VNS
          </div>
          <div class="timeline__event-title text-center">Vimalvasahi</div>
          
          <!-- ASPECT RATIO 16:9, DIMENSION OF IMAGES SHOULD BE 320X180 -->
          <img class="timeline__event-image" src="/static/images/timeline/vimalvasahi.jpg" alt="Vimalvasahi"/>
          
          <!-- DESCRIPTION SHOULD BE LESS THAN 270 CHARACTERS -->
          <div class="timeline__event-descr">Minister Vimal was the commander of King Bhimdev of Gujarat. Once influenced by Sri Dharmaghoshasuri, he wanted to atone for the sins of wars. Acharya Shri asked him to renovate Abu Tirth. So he built a magnificient temple with amazing artwork, due to which Abu is renowned in the world.</div>
          
        </div>
        
        <div class="timeline__event timeline__eventtype-mandir">
          <div class="timeline__event-date">
              1612 VNS
          </div>
          <div class="timeline__event-title text-center">Antariksh Parshwanath</div>
          
          <!-- ASPECT RATIO 16:9, DIMENSION OF IMAGES SHOULD BE 320X180 -->
          <img class="timeline__event-image" src="/static/images/timeline/antariksh.jpg" alt="Antariksh Parshwanath"/>
          
          <!-- DESCRIPTION SHOULD BE LESS THAN 270 CHARACTERS -->
          <div class="timeline__event-descr">A Parshwanath idol built in clay during Ramayana, was worshiped by a Dev in Vidarbha. Elchipur King, suffering from leprosy, was cured by it. The king tried to take it to his city. However, it stayed put in the way. So he built a temple right there, now known as Antriksh Parshwanath.</div>
          
        </div>
        
        <div class="timeline__event timeline__eventtype-raja">
          <div class="timeline__event-date">
              1669 VNS
          </div>
          <div class="timeline__event-title text-center">Kumarpal</div>
          
          <!-- ASPECT RATIO 16:9, DIMENSION OF IMAGES SHOULD BE 320X180 -->
          <img class="timeline__event-image" src="/static/images/timeline/kumarpal.jpg" alt="Kumarpal"/>
          
          <!-- DESCRIPTION SHOULD BE LESS THAN 270 CHARACTERS -->
          <div class="timeline__event-descr">Kumarapal conquered 14 countries post his coronation on the throne of Gujarat. With the preaching of Acharya Shri Hemachandrasuri, Kumarapal proclaimed ahimsa, took the vows of Jain Shravak, made seven pilgrimage, constructed 21 libraries and 1444 new temples and renovated 1800 temples.</div>
          
        </div>
        
        <div class="timeline__event timeline__eventtype-mandir">
          <div class="timeline__event-date">
              1683 VNS
          </div>
          <div class="timeline__event-title text-center">Shatrunjay&#x27;s 14th Renovation</div>
          
          <!-- ASPECT RATIO 16:9, DIMENSION OF IMAGES SHOULD BE 320X180 -->
          <img class="timeline__event-image" src="/static/images/timeline/Jinnordhar14.jpg" alt="Shatrunjay&#x27;s 14th Renovation"/>
          
          <!-- DESCRIPTION SHOULD BE LESS THAN 270 CHARACTERS -->
          <div class="timeline__event-descr">Bahad was the minister of Siddharaj and an officer of high rank of Kumarapal. He rebuilt the wooden temple using marble. He got it consecrated by Hemachandrasuri. This temple still exists today. The news bearer of the temple’s construction progress was given 16 silver tongues.</div>
          
        </div>
        
        <div class="timeline__event timeline__eventtype-raja">
          <div class="timeline__event-date">
              1746 VNS
          </div>
          <div class="timeline__event-title text-center">Vastupal and Tejpla</div>
          
          <!-- ASPECT RATIO 16:9, DIMENSION OF IMAGES SHOULD BE 320X180 -->
          <img class="timeline__event-image" src="/static/images/timeline/vastupaltejpal.jpg" alt="Vastupal and Tejpla"/>
          
          <!-- DESCRIPTION SHOULD BE LESS THAN 270 CHARACTERS -->
          <div class="timeline__event-descr">In the beginning the brothers were ministers of King Veeradhaval. Their shrewdness led to the re-organization of the Hindu kings of Gujarat, Rajasthan and Maharashtra. Together they won a total of 63 wars. They considered Acahrya Sri Vijayanasuri as their religious mentor.</div>
          
        </div>
        
        <div class="timeline__event timeline__eventtype-default">
          <div class="timeline__event-date">
              1755 VNS
          </div>
          <div class="timeline__event-title text-center">Tapagaccha</div>
          
          <!-- DESCRIPTION SHOULD BE LESS THAN 270 CHARACTERS -->
          <div class="timeline__event-descr">Sri Jagachandrasuri was the 44th in the lineage of Shri Sudharma Swami. While doing ayambil for twelve years, he came to Mewar. Rana Jaitrasinh was impressed with him and honoured him with the title &quot;Tapa&quot;. Hence, the Shramana tradition of Lord Mahavira started being called as Tapagachh.</div>
          
        </div>
        
        <div class="timeline__event timeline__eventtype-mandir">
          <div class="timeline__event-date">
              1780 VNS
          </div>
          <div class="timeline__event-title text-center">Renovation of Shankeshwar Tirth</div>
          
          <!-- ASPECT RATIO 16:9, DIMENSION OF IMAGES SHOULD BE 320X180 -->
          <img class="timeline__event-image" src="/static/images/timeline/Shankeshwar.jpg" alt="Renovation of Shankeshwar Tirth"/>
          
          <!-- DESCRIPTION SHOULD BE LESS THAN 270 CHARACTERS -->
          <div class="timeline__event-descr">The king of Jhinjhuvada suffered from leprosy and to  cure that he tried several remedies. He finally prayed to Suryanarayana said – Worship the God in Shankheshwar and you will be cured of the disease. The King renovated the shrine in Vik. Sam. in 1310.</div>
          
        </div>
        
        <div class="timeline__event timeline__eventtype-mandir">
          <div class="timeline__event-date">
              1966 VNS
          </div>
          <div class="timeline__event-title text-center">Ranakpur</div>
          
          <!-- ASPECT RATIO 16:9, DIMENSION OF IMAGES SHOULD BE 320X180 -->
          <img class="timeline__event-image" src="/static/images/timeline/Ranakpur.jpg" alt="Ranakpur"/>
          
          <!-- DESCRIPTION SHOULD BE LESS THAN 270 CHARACTERS -->
          <div class="timeline__event-descr">Once Sanghvi Dharanshah saw the Nalinigulam-Viman in a dream and decided to build as a magnificent temple as he saw. Later, a grand three-storey 45-feet tall temple was built by him in Ranakpur with 14 pillars which was inaugurated by Acharya Somasundarasuri in Vik. Sam. 1496.</div>
          
        </div>
        
        <div class="timeline__event timeline__eventtype-mandir">
          <div class="timeline__event-date">
              2047 VNS
          </div>
          <div class="timeline__event-title text-center">16th Renovation of Shatrunjay</div>
          
          <!-- ASPECT RATIO 16:9, DIMENSION OF IMAGES SHOULD BE 320X180 -->
          <img class="timeline__event-image" src="/static/images/timeline/ShatrunjayAdinath.jpg" alt="16th Renovation of Shatrunjay"/>
          
          <!-- DESCRIPTION SHOULD BE LESS THAN 270 CHARACTERS -->
          <div class="timeline__event-descr">Muslim aggressors broke the main idol on Shatrunjaya. Karma Shah of Udaipur built a new idol at an auspicious time, which was consecrated by Shri Vidyamandanasuri. At the time of pratistha, God breathed seven times. This idol is the mulnayak on the peak of Shatrunjaya today.</div>
          
        </div>
        
        <div class="timeline__event timeline__eventtype-default">
          <div class="timeline__event-date">
              2078 VNS
          </div>
          <div class="timeline__event-title text-center">Akbar</div>
          
          <!-- ASPECT RATIO 16:9, DIMENSION OF IMAGES SHOULD BE 320X180 -->
          <img class="timeline__event-image" src="/static/images/timeline/Akbar.jpg" alt="Akbar"/>
          
          <!-- DESCRIPTION SHOULD BE LESS THAN 270 CHARACTERS -->
          <div class="timeline__event-descr">Preached by Acharya Shri Hiravijayuri, Akbar proclaimed 6 months of non violence every year in his 12 districts, stopped &quot;jaziya&quot;, stopped confiscating wealth of childless couple, stopped consuming the tongue of 500 birds in his breakfast and honored Acharya Sri with the title of Jagadguru.</div>
          
        </div>
        
        <div class="timeline__event timeline__eventtype-default">
          <div class="timeline__event-date">
              2378 VNS
          </div>
          <div class="timeline__event-title text-center">Protection of Samvegi Path</div>
          
          <!-- DESCRIPTION SHOULD BE LESS THAN 270 CHARACTERS -->
          <div class="timeline__event-descr">Shri Budhvijay opposed accumulation of wealth by sadhus and residence in Jain Temple and revived Murti Puja. Facing hardshop alone, he revived the true path of Tirthankar Kevali Bhagwant</div>
          
        </div>
        
        <div class="timeline__event timeline__eventtype-default">
          <div class="timeline__event-date">
              2547 VNS
          </div>
          <div class="timeline__event-title text-center">Today&#x27;s Sadhu Samuday</div>
          
          <!-- ASPECT RATIO 16:9, DIMENSION OF IMAGES SHOULD BE 320X180 -->
          <img class="timeline__event-image" src="/static/images/timeline/JainSadhu.jpg" alt="Today&#x27;s Sadhu Samuday"/>
          
          <!-- DESCRIPTION SHOULD BE LESS THAN 270 CHARACTERS -->
          <div class="timeline__event-descr">Today, there are 17,155 Sadhu – Sadhviji combined in all the four major sects, including Svetambara, Digambar Sthanakwasi and Terapanti. The Shwetambar Murtipujak is the largest of the Sadhu community with a total of around 10715 monks.</div>
          
        </div>
        
      </div>       
    </div> 
